<!--
  SCENARIO 2 — Wrong base class inferred for XAML-only class (CS1061)

  This file has x:Class but NO code-behind (.xaml.cs).
  The XAML root is <Grid>, so the generated partial class must extend Grid.
  Grid inherits Panel.Children (UIElementCollection), which callers rely on.

  Without the fix: WxsgGenerateCSharpWpfTmpStubs falls back to UserControl as the
  base type when no code-behind is found, because UserControl is the most common root.
  But UserControl has no Children property — it has Content (from ContentControl).

  Error (with wrong base = UserControl, in _wpftmp, via PanelHost.xaml.cs):
    PanelHost.xaml.cs(18,25): error CS1061:
      'ItemsPanel' does not contain a definition for 'Children'

  Fix: wpfTypeMap now maps "Grid" → global::System.Windows.Controls.Grid so the stub
  correctly declares:
    public partial class ItemsPanel : global::System.Windows.Controls.Grid {
        public void InitializeComponent() { }
    }

  Real-world origin: BookmarkPadContent.xaml in ICSharpCode.SharpDevelop, which is
  a Grid-rooted XAML-only class. BookmarkPad.cs then does:
    this.control.Children.Add(toolbar);
-->
<Grid x:Class="WpfTmpStubIssue.Scenario2_WrongBase.ItemsPanel"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml">
    <ListView Name="listView"
              x:FieldModifier="public" />
</Grid>
